The EEA agreement is an agreement between the EU and the three EFTA countries (Iceland, Liechtenstein and Norway) which allows the EFTA countries to participate in the EU internal market without joining the EU. The EEA agreement is based on the same principles as the EU internal market, but it does not include the EU’s common agricultural and fisheries policies or the common commercial policy.
